# Finding 077
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Billing provider SDK name resolver duplicated across packages
- File + line(s): `packages/billing/billing-provider-core/src/shared/providerConstants.js:10-16`, `packages/billing/billing-service-core/src/shared/constants.js:183-189`, `packages/billing/billing-knex-mysql/src/shared/constants.js:183-189`
- Why it can drift/fail: Provider SDK name resolution logic is duplicated across three billing packages. If provider defaults or naming rules change, they must be updated in multiple locations.
- Concrete impact: Inconsistent provider SDK naming between provider core, service core, and storage layer.
- Exact remediation: Centralize provider constants and helper functions in `billing-provider-core` and import them from service/knex packages.
